The defendant Dameko M Hollis Jr was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Dameko M Hollis Jr is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Dameko M Hollis Jr was found guilty of Possession of THC, an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(e).

records.addlTxt:
Statements made as to Sentencing by both counsel and Defendant.

AS TO COUNT 1:  Defendant sentenced to serve 45 DAYS  in the House of Correction, to run consecutive to 14CM002381, and any other sentence, with credit for 18 days time served.  Huber privileges under Sec.303.08 Wis. Stats. to apply for work and school. 

Court IMPOSED AND STAYED the sentence and placed Defendant on Probation with the State of Wisconsin, Department of Corrections for a period of 1 YEAR to run concurrent as to case 14CM002381 with the following conditions as to Probation:
*  No new law violations reaching the level of a probable cause finding.
*  Cooperate with agent.
*  Pay all mandatory costs, surcharges, assessments, supervision fees during the period of probation.  Failure to pay shall result in a Civil Judgment with tax intercept.
*  Maintain full time / part time employment and or schooling.
*  ABSOLUTE SOBRIETY.
*  AODA assessment with follow up care and treatment.
*  Random urine screens with no positive results.  No association with drug users, drug dealers, drug houses, or drug dealings.
*  Community service of 15 hours.

Court will consider expungement if Defendant successfully completes all conditions of probation with no new law violations reaching the level of a probable cause finding.

Received and filed with court:
*  Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief Form
*  Pretrial Incarceration Credit Form

Defendant Dameko M Hollis in court with attorney Gregory A. Renden.  Defendant Dameko M Hollis in custody.  Brittany Skye Kachingwe appeared for the State of Wisconsin. 

AS TO COUNT 1:    Defendant waived rights and pled GUILTY.  Guilty Plea Questionnaire received and filed.  Defendant examined as to the plea.  Parties stipulate to the facts of the complaint as a basis for a guilty plea.  Court found the Defendant guilty as charged in the complaint.  Judgment of Conviction entered.  

AS TO COUNT 2:  On motion of the State Court ordered Count 2 DISMISSED AND READ-IN.

Court orders defendant TURNED OVER to JUSTICE Point for Supervision.  DEFENDANT to be monitored by drug testing.  No use or possession of controlled substances without a valid prescription.  Defendant advised it is a requirement to attend all future court proceedings.  Failure to comply with conditions of bail may result in an additional charge of bail jumping.

Defendant Dameko M Hollis in court with attorney Christopher John Ertl.  Defendant Dameko M Hollis in custody.  Carole Manchester appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Court Clerk:  bm
  Defendant is advised due to lower pending case this case is assigned to Judge Dee, Branch 37.  Court reviewed the complaint and found probable cause.  Defendant advised of right to counsel and complaint given to defendant's attorney.  Defendant plead not guilty.  DEFENDANT IS INDIGENT AND QUALIFIES FOR PUBLIC DEFENDER REPRESENTATION.  Status conference scheduled for July 24, 2015 at 08:30 am.
Defendant in Custody, Court appearance today in Intake Court, Room 137A.
